Suggested fix: in `rch/src/main.rs` early dispatch, detect attached TTY on stdin and print a short hint pointing at `rch --help` and `rch hook test` instead of silently waiting.

Pseudocode:

```rust
if std::io::stdin().is_terminal() {
    eprintln!("rch is running in PreToolUse hook mode (waiting for JSON on stdin).");
    eprintln!("For human help:        rch --help");
    eprintln!("To test the hook:      rch hook test");
    eprintln!("To launch the TUI:     rch dashboard");
    eprintln!("To exit:               press Ctrl-D or Ctrl-C");
}
```

Symptom evidence: cass shows agents typing `rch help` (no dashes) or just `rch` and getting no output, then guessing about whether the binary is installed correctly. Mirrors the same UX cliff the cass skill calls out ("never bare `cass`").

